summary: CAN WE TALK ABOUT HOW HARRY PROPOSES? LIKE ON THEIR 5TH ANNIVERSARY DINNER OR SOMETHING AND THAT NIGHT SHES SO SHY AND BLUSHY...
question: CAN WE TALK ABOUT HOW HARRY PROPOSES? LIKE ON THEIR 5TH ANNIVERSARY DINNER OR SOMETHING AND THAT NIGHT SHES SO SHY AND BLUSHY HARRY IS JUST IN AWE AND HAPPY THAT SHE SAID YES
answer:
YES WE CAN!!!

for some reason, i imagine it being somewhere tropical. He has his palm trees shirt on and blue shorts, she has that cream colored dress that drove him crazy when he saw her in it because “fuck, can’t believe you’re mine” and they’re both sun kissed just right, tanning lines, wavy beach hair and all.

It’s night and they’re going to dinner on the beach because no matter how cliché this is, everyone secretly wants it. They’re sitting on some sort of like, a mattress on the sand under a very simple gazebo that has fairy lights that made them look like they came straight outta tumblr, roses on the table and the sound of crashing waves.
They’d be talking about his tour, her work, his family and hers. It’s when she’s telling him how proud she is of him that he has THAT smile. You know that smile you smile at someone and it’s more of to yourself because you can’t believe that you have that person in your life and you’re just so grateful? Yes, it’s THAT smile.

Then as if on cue, “I love You More Than You’ll Ever Know” by Amy Winehouse starts playing and by the wide smile on Harry’s face, she’s laughing and she’s standing up with him. Harry drags her to the sand, their bare feet embracing the tiny grains and their arms around each other. His hands are on her waist, her arms around his neck and they’re looking at each other; no verbal conversation, just this.

“I can be anything you demand.” Harry whispers with the song, his head leaning to rest on hers after he kisses her hair and her forehead is on his chest and they’re swaying together. When the song is done and only the sea waves were heard, he takes his chance.
They still have their arms around each other, spiritually and physically connected that this moment just feels infinite.

Harry pulls away and he looks down at her with a smile and the butterflies in his stomach are getting too much for him to handle. He’s tucking her hair that keeps flying in front of her face behind her ears and he’s caressing her blushing cheeks. He leans down and gives her a sweet peck, “You know I love you, right?”

She hums, biting her lip and playing with his hair on his nape of neck and nods, “Right.”
And they’re talking soooo softly.

He continues, “Do you also know that it physically pains me when I’m away from you? When I’m touring and you’re at home and we’re oceans away and I just want to hold you. Just want you with me everywhere I go. You’ve seen me at my worst and my best, supported me through everything, assured me when I was doubtful, held me when I was insecure. It’s safe to say that I can’t live without you,”

She has tears in her eyes by now. She’s smiling up at him and she just listens.

“I know I tend to get clingy sometimes. Feels like I want to love on you full-time, gorgeous. And I can,” He smiles wider, taking the velvet blue ring box from his pocket before kneeling on his knee, looking up at her. She’s full on crying now. She gasps, she has her hands covering her mouth and she’s laughing in disbelief at the same time. “So Y/N, love, would you do me the honor of spending the rest of your life with me and please, marry me?”

She instantly lets a “Yes! Yes! A million times yes!” And they’re both laughing and crying and still in disbelief when he slides the ring on her finger before engulfing her in a tight hug, both shaking from crying and laughing.

“I love you. I love you so much, gorgeous.”

who’s crying
